

/* ============================================================================
 * Name:       ex7
 * Written by: Sahar Itzhak, Ron Efraim
 * ID:         308389485, 204661425
 * Login:      saharyz, ronef
 * Program:    RPC connection
 * ============================================================================
 *
 * This program has a server and a client and connects them through rpc.
 * Serever- has 3 functions:
 * 1) is_lowercase: checks if the string entered is all lowercase.
 * 2) digit_sum: gets a rational number and adds it's digits.
 * 3) check_dup: gets 2 strings and tells how many same letters it has.
 * Client- connects to server and user enters a number:
 * 1: for is_lowercase function.
 * 2: for digit_sum function.
 * 3: for check_dup function.
 * 0: to end program.
 * else: wrong input- exits.

 * Compile: rpcgen ex7.x
   gcc -Wall ex7a1.c ex7_svc.c -lm -o server
   gcc -Wall ex7a2.c ex7_clnt.c -o client
 * Run: server &
   client <IP>

 * Input: 1- for lowercase, 2- for digit sum, 3- check duplication, 0- exit.

 * Output: 1- is/isn't lowercase, 2- the sum of digits, 
   3- how many chars are similar, 0- exit.
 * ============================================================================
 */
